Add a defined field<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
ADD FIELD likes INT DEFAULT 0;
</code></pre> Drop a defined field and scrub data<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
DROP FIELD user_id;
</code></pre> Drop a defined field but keep data as free field<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
DROP FIELD user_id KEEP;
</code></pre> Drop a free field<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
DROP FREE FIELD likes;
</code></pre> Modify a defined field<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
MODIFY FIELD replies ARRAY(INT) REFERENCES users(user_id);
</code></pre> Modify a field with a cast<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
MODIFY FIELD post_id INT USING CAST(post_id AS INT);
</code></pre> Rename a defined field<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
RENAME FIELD replies TO user_replies;
</code></pre> Rename a collection<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
RENAME TO user_posts;
</code></pre> Add a constraint<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
ADD CONSTRAINT CHK_content CHECK (content IS NOT NULL);
</code></pre> Drop a constraint<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
DROP CONSTRAINT CHK_content;
</code></pre> Modify a constraint<pre><code>ALTER COLLECTION posts
MODIFY CONSTRAINT CHK_content CHECK (content IS NOT NULL AND content != '');
</code></pre>

Add a column<pre><code>ALTER TABLE users
ADD COLUMN phone_number VARCHAR(10) DEFAULT '000-000-0000';
</code></pre> Drop a column<pre><code>ALTER TABLE users
DROP COLUMN email;
</code></pre> Modify a column<pre><code>ALTER TABLE users
MODIFY COLUMN phone_number INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
</code></pre> Modify a column with a cast<pre><code>ALTER TABLE users
MODIFY COLUMN phone_number INT USING CAST(REPLACE(phone_number, '-', '') AS INT);
</code></pre> Rename a column<pre><code>ALTER TABLE users
RENAME COLUMN phone_number TO phone;
</code></pre> Rename a table<pre><code>ALTER TABLE users
RENAME TO user_data;
</code></pre> Add a named constraint<pre><code>ALTER TABLE users
ADD CONSTRAINT CHK_username UNIQUE;
</code></pre> Drop a constraint<pre><code>ALTER TABLE users
DROP CONSTRAINT CHK_username;
</code></pre> Modify a constraint<pre><code>ALTER TABLE users
MODIFY CONSTRAINT CHK_username UNIQUE NOT NULL;
</code></pre>

Fully schemaless collection<pre><code>-- This will include the auto-generated _id field.
CREATE COLLECTION posts;
</code></pre> Collection with a secondary key<pre><code>-- This will create a composite of _id + user_id
CREATE COLLECTION posts (
    user_id INT SECONDARY KEY
);
</code></pre> Collection with defined fields<pre><code>-- No primary or secondary key's are defined, so this has an _id field.
CREATE COLLECTION posts (
    user_id INT REFERENCES users(user_id),
    content JSON,
    created_at DATETIME AUTONOW,
    last_updated DATETIME AUTO
);
</code></pre> Collection with multiple secondary keys<pre><code>-- No PRIMARY KEY, so it will be _id + order_id + event_type
CREATE COLLECTION order_events (
    order_id SECONDARY KEY,
    event_type SECONDARY KEY,
    payload JSON
);
</code></pre>

Create a new database<pre><code>CREATE DATABASE my_database;
</code></pre> Create a database only if it does not already exist<pre><code>CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS my_database;
</code></pre>

Drop a collection<pre><code>DROP COLLECTION posts;
</code></pre> Drop a collection if it exists<pre><code>DROP COLLECTION IF EXISTS posts;
</code></pre> Drop a collection with one dependency<pre><code>DROP COLLECTION posts CASCADE;
</code></pre> Drop a collection with a specific depth<pre><code>DROP COLLECTION posts CASCADE 2;
</code></pre> Drop a collection and all dependencies regardless of depth<pre><code>DROP COLLECTION posts CASCADE INFINITY;
</code></pre> Drop a collection and set all foreign key references to null<pre><code>DROP COLLECTION posts CASCADE 2 SET NULL;
</code></pre> Drop a collection and set all foreign key references to their default<pre><code>DROP COLLECTION posts CASCADE 2 SET DEFAULT;
</code></pre> Drop a collection and drop all dependent objects<pre><code>DROP COLLECTION posts CASCADE 2 DROP;
</code></pre> Truncate a collection<pre><code>TRUNCATE COLLECTION posts;
</code></pre> Truncate a collection and reset autoincrement counters<pre><code>TRUNCATE COLLECTION posts RESTART IDENTITY;
</code></pre>

Drop a database<pre><code>DROP DATABASE my_database CONFIRM 'my_database';
</code></pre> Drop a database if it exists<pre><code>DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS my_database CONFIRM 'my_database';
</code></pre> Truncate a database<pre><code>TRUNCATE DATABASE my_database CONFIRM 'my_database';
</code></pre> Truncate a database and reset all autoincrement counters<pre><code>TRUNCATE DATABASE my_database CONFIRM 'my_database' RESTART IDENTITY;
</code></pre>

Drop a table<pre><code>DROP TABLE users;
</code></pre> Drop a table if it exists<pre><code>DROP TABLE IF EXISTS users;
</code></pre> Drop a table with one dependency<pre><code>DROP TABLE users CASCADE;
</code></pre> Drop a table with a specific depth<pre><code>DROP TABLE users CASCADE 2;
</code></pre> Drop a table and all dependencies regardless of depth<pre><code>DROP TABLE users CASCADE INFINITY;
</code></pre> Drop a table and set all foreign key references to null<pre><code>DROP TABLE users CASCADE 2 SET NULL;
</code></pre> Drop a table and set all foreign key references to their default<pre><code>DROP TABLE users CASCADE 2 SET DEFAULT;
</code></pre> Drop a table and drop all dependent objects<pre><code>DROP TABLE users CASCADE 2 DROP;
</code></pre> Truncate a table<pre><code>TRUNCATE TABLE users;
</code></pre> Truncate a table and reset autoincrement counters<pre><code>TRUNCATE TABLE users RESTART IDENTITY;
</code></pre>

Single table<pre><code>SELECT users.username, users.first_name
FROM users;
</code></pre> Single collection<pre><code>SELECT posts::content, posts::created_at
FROM posts;
</code></pre> Table with alias<pre><code>SELECT u.username, u.first_name
FROM users AS u;
</code></pre> Subquery as source<pre><code>SELECT active.username
FROM (
    SELECT users.username
    FROM users
    WHERE users.last_login &gt; '2024-01-01'
) AS active;
</code></pre> Multiple sources with a join<pre><code>SELECT users.username, posts::content
FROM users, posts(user_id);
</code></pre>

Select specific columns from a table<pre><code>SELECT users.username, users.first_name, users.last_name
FROM users;
</code></pre> Select all columns from a table<pre><code>SELECT users.* FROM users;
</code></pre> Select fields from a collection<pre><code>SELECT posts::content, posts::created_at FROM posts;
</code></pre> Mix table columns and collection fields<pre><code>SELECT
    users.username,
    posts::content,
    posts::created_at
FROM posts
LEFT JOIN users ON users.user_id = posts.user_id;
</code></pre> Function call with alias<pre><code>SELECT
    users.username,
    COUNT_ARRAY(comments::likes) AS num_likes
FROM comments
LEFT JOIN users ON users.user_id = comments.user_id;
</code></pre> DISTINCT on a column<pre><code>SELECT DISTINCT users.username FROM users;
</code></pre>

Basic filter<pre><code>SELECT users.username
FROM users
WHERE users.status = 'active';
</code></pre> Multiple conditions<pre><code>SELECT users.username
FROM users
WHERE users.age &gt; 18 AND users.status = 'active';
</code></pre> Filter on collection free field<pre><code>SELECT posts::content
FROM posts
WHERE posts::likes &gt; 10;
</code></pre> NULL and MISSING checks<pre><code>SELECT posts::content
FROM posts
WHERE posts::likes IS NOT NULL OR MISSING;
</code></pre> Pattern matching<pre><code>SELECT users.username
FROM users
WHERE users.username ILIKE 'john%';
</code></pre> IN with subquery<pre><code>SELECT users.username
FROM users
WHERE users.user_id IN (
    SELECT orders.user_id
    FROM orders
    WHERE orders.total &gt; 100
);
</code></pre> EXISTS<pre><code>SELECT users.username
FROM users
WHERE EXISTS (
    SELECT posts::post_id
    FROM posts
    WHERE posts::user_id = users.user_id
);
</code></pre>
